#1. Load Data ---
fevData <- read.csv("./data/fev.csv", header = TRUE)

#2. Format the data ---
# convers sex and smoke to labelled factors
fevData$sex = factor(fevData$sex, 
                     levels = c(0,1),
                     labels = c("Female", "Male"))

fevData$smoke = factor(fevData$smoke, 
                       levels = c(0,1),
                       labels = c("Non-Smoker", "Smoker"))

#Convert height from inches to centimeters
fevData$height = fevData$height * 2.54

#Convert age to numeric
fevData$age <- as.numeric(fevData$age)

#confirm the records are correct
str(fevData)

  geom_histogram()
plot1
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

#Try and change the bin width
plot1 <- ggplot(fevData, aes(x = age)) + geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.1)
plot1

#Fill the smoking status by age with smoke
plot1 <- ggplot(fevData, aes(x = age, fill=smoke)) + geom_histogram(alpha=1, binwidth = 1)
plot1

#Add some labels
plot1 <- ggplot(fevData, aes(x = age, fill = smoke)) + 
  geom_histogram(alpha = .5, binwidth = 1) +
  labs(x = "Age of the participants in years",
       y = "Count of participants",
       title = "Histogram of smokers and non smokers per age group",
       fill = "Smoking Status")
plot1

#Use a theme
plot1 <- plot1 + theme_bw()
plot1

#A different way
plot1 <- ggplot(fevData, aes(x = age, fill = smoke)) + 
  geom_histogram(alpha = 0.45, binwidth = 1) + 
  labs(x = "Age (years)",
       y = "Count", 
       title = "Histogram of age by smoking status",
       fill = "Smoking status",
       caption = "FEV data from Tager et al (1979)") +
  theme_void()
plot1

#Facets
plot1 <- ggplot(fevData, aes(x = age, fill = smoke)) + 
  geom_histogram(alpha = 0.45, binwidth = 1) + 
  facet_wrap(~smoke) +
  labs(x = "Age (years)",
       y = "Count", 
       title = "Histogram of age by smoking status",
       fill = "Smoking status",
       caption = "FEV data from Tager et al (1979)") +
  theme_minimal()
plot1

#Stratified by sex
plot1 <- ggplot(fevData, aes(x = age, fill = smoke)) + 
  geom_histogram(alpha = 0.45, binwidth = 1) + 
  facet_wrap(~ sex) +
  labs(x = "Age (years)",
       y = "Count", 
       title = "Histogram of age by smoking status and sex",
       fill = "Smoking status",
       caption = "FEV data from Tager et al (1979)") +
  theme_minimal()
plot1

#Boxplot
plot1 <- ggplot(fevData, aes(x = age, y = smoke, fill = smoke)) + 
  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.45) + 
  facet_wrap(~sex) +
  labs(x = "Age (years)",
       y = "Smoking Status", 
       title = "Boxplots of age by smoking status and sex",
       caption = "FEV data from Tager et al (1979)") +
  theme_minimal() + theme(legend.position = "none")
plot1

#Density Plot
plot1 <- ggplot(fevData, aes(x = age, fill = smoke)) + 
  geom_density(alpha = 0.45) + 
  facet_wrap(~sex) +
  labs(x = "Age (years)",
       y = "Density", 
       title = "Density Plot of age by smoking status and sex",
       fill =  "Smoking Status",
       caption = "FEV data from Tager et al (1979)") +
  theme_minimal()
plot1

#Scatter plot of age vs height
  scatterPlot <- ggplot(data=fevData, aes(x = age, y = height)) +
  geom_point()
  scatterPlot

#Colour by groups
  scatterPlot <- ggplot(data = fevData, aes(x = age, y = height, colour = sex)) +
  geom_point()
  scatterPlot

#Customising colours
  myColours <- c("#ffb366", "blue")
  scatterPlot <- ggplot(data = fevData, aes(x = age, y = height, colour = sex)) +
  geom_point() + scale_color_manual(values = myColours)
  scatterPlot

#Use color brewer
  scatterPlot <- ggplot(data = fevData, aes(x = age, y = height, colour = sex)) +
  geom_point() + scale_color_brewer(palette = "Accent")
  scatterPlot

# Brewer colours are Accent,  Dark2 (colour blind friendly), Paired (colour blind friendly), Pastel1
# Pastel2, Set1, Set2 (colour blind friendly), Set3

  #Add a regression line
  scatterPlot <- ggplot(data = fevData, aes(x = age, y = height, colour = sex, fill = sex)) +
    geom_point() + 
    geom_smooth(method = "loess", se = F) + 
    scale_color_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +
    scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Dark2")
  scatterPlot
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

#Add some labels
  scatterPlot <- ggplot(data = fevData, aes(x = age, y = height, colour = sex, fill = sex)) +
    geom_point() + 
    geom_smooth(method = "loess", se = T) + 
    scale_color_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +
    scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +
    labs(x = "Age (years)",
       y = "Height (cm)") +
  theme_classic()
  scatterPlot
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

  #This also needs some colours for the chart
  violin <- ggplot(data = fevData, aes(y = height, x = sex)) + geom_violin()
